The paper deals with mechanism design and optimization in auction settings, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses optimization techniques and algorithms, which are commonly studied in computer science (cs.DS, cs.IT). The use of black-box calls to welfare approximation suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), while the focus on revenue and welfare maximization is a core topic in computational economics (cs.EC).
